 <body>
  <p>Administrators can create a new resource from scratch or create an extension of an existing resource if you need work on data that are not part of the out-of-the-box data model.</p> 
  <ol>
   <li><p>From <strong>Administration</strong> &gt; <strong>Development</strong> &gt; <strong>Custom Resources</strong>, click the <strong>Create</strong> button.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Choose the action you want to perform:</p> 
    <ul>
     <li><p><strong>Create a new resource</strong>: Enter the <strong>Label</strong> and <strong>ID</strong> fields. The <strong>ID</strong> field is mandatory. If you leave the Label field empty, it will automatically be completed from the ID.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/schema_extension_2.png" title="" /></li>
     <li><p><strong>Extend an existing resource</strong>: Select the resource you want to extend.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/schema_extension_10.png" title="" /></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><p>Click <strong>Create</strong> to create the resource, which will then take on the <strong>Draft</strong> status in case of new resource or the <strong>Editing</strong> status in case of extension.</p> </li>
  </ol>
  <p>The new resource is created and can now be configured.</p> 
